OL,3,CMan guilty of manslaughter after
OL,4,Cstabbing in St Pauls
OL,6,FThree weeks later, on 5 March, he
OL,7,Fborrowed a car and was seen driving
OL,8,Faround the St Pauls area for more than
OL,9,Fan hour until he found Alex and,
OL,10,Fduring a brief confrontation, fatally
OL,11,Fstabbed him in the upper thigh.
OL,13,FAlex was taken to hospital by a taxi
OL,14,Fdriver, but despite the efforts of
OL,15,Fmedics, he sadly died a short while
OL,16,Flater.
OL,18,FMalcolm was arrested that night and
OL,19,Fsubsequently charged by detectives
OL,20,Ffrom the Major Crime Investigation
OL,21,FTeam.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
